        "text": "This place is awesome. The teachers are so warm and welcoming, our daughter started here in April, and we were sad to leave in August because we were moving. This was the first daycare she has been to , and the staff did everything to make a smooth transition. They had floating teachers to help with the new children and give them on one one attention, the teachers all make the children feel sooooo loved and welcomed. I've observed the way that they handle conflict with other kids, and tantrums, tip-top in their empathy and de-escalating. There's a huge indoor gym where kids can play and get physical activity on colder days, and a pretty decent outdoor spot with a good assortment of age-appropriate playground equipment. They provide meals for your kids, and take them out for picnics and walks to get fresh air- weather permitting. Flexible plans for new-to-daycare parents to transition their kids (which many daycares don't allow), and they also helped during our move to accommodate her an extra day after our agreement.\nLove love love chapter 1 downtown.\n\nanother great thing thats unique about this daycare- the walls between classes go up halfway- so teachers can see each other across classes, which increases accountability and transparency and allows for easy assistance if needed in one room!\n\nand did i mention their prices are one of the cheapest, with the lowest deposit for daycares in downtown calgary?\n\nThank you Chapter one team for a wonderful time!",
