        "rating": 5,
        "relativeTimeDescription": "3 months ago",
        "text": "As a parent, I have a completely different perspective on the daycare and I feel compelled to share my thoughts in response to Jamie's review. While I understand that Jamie's experience may not have been positive, I want to highlight some important aspects that were overlooked.\n\nFirst and foremost, I have  been extremely pleased with the staff and the owner of the daycare. They have been consistently attentive, caring, and professional throughout my child's time there. The dedication and passion they demonstrate in their work is commendable.\n\nRegarding the incident during nap time, it's important to consider that children may sometimes misinterpret or misconstrue statements made by educators. I trust that the daycare staff would not intentionally say anything hurtful or promote gender bias. However, I appreciate Jamie bringing this to our attention, and I'm confident that the daycare management will address the matter appropriately.\n\nRegarding the food, I acknowledge that individual preferences can vary. However, it's important to note that the daycare makes an effort to provide nutritious meals for all children. I have personally witnessed the staff ensuring a balanced and healthy diet for the kids, taking into account dietary restrictions and allergies.\n\nRegarding the disciplinary actions witnessed by Jamie, it's crucial to maintain a safe and disciplined environment for all children. While it may be distressing for some kids to witness disciplinary measures, it's important to understand that the staff's intention is to teach valuable lessons and promote positive behavior. I have seen instances where the staff handles disciplinary matters with fairness and sensitivity.\n\nI want to emphasize that my child has had a positive experience at this daycare. The nurturing environment, engaging activities, and supportive staff have played a significant role in his growth and development. It's unfortunate that Jamie's perception differs from mine, but I believe it's important to consider multiple perspectives when evaluating the quality of a daycare.\n\nIn conclusion, I respect Jamie's decision to share their experience, but I wanted to offer my own perspective as a parent who has been satisfied with the daycare services. Each child's experience can be unique, and I believe it's essential for parents to visit the daycare, interact with the staff, and make an informed decision based on their own observations and the needs of their child.",
