        "rating": 1,
        "relativeTimeDescription": "3 months ago",
        "text": "My son went to this daycare during  kindergarten and now he is about to finish grade one.  Every time we drive by the centre he keeps telling me a year later how much he hated it. I‚Äôve debated writing a review but since he continues to tell me how bad his experience was at this daycare I‚Äôm impelled to write some of his feedback that he says about his time at this centre.\n\nOne thing I reported as a parent to his teacher after he came home one day distraught;  was how upset he was because one of the educators watching his class during nap time told them all that ‚Äúgirls are better than boys‚Äù    This was extremely unprofessional and hurtful. My son is quite sensitive and always wants to be good so he took it very hard and personal. Even though he was listening and trying to be quiet.\n\nOther things he‚Äôs expressed and shared about being there was how awful the sandwiches and wraps were to eat at lunch. He found the food unappealing.\n\nHe witnessed other kids who were being ‚Äúbad‚Äù getting yelled at and taken to the office for punishment. This made him feel uneasy and felt bad for these kids who he could hear still getting yelled at in the office. Overall he found some of the staff to be rude, mean and very strict to all the kids.\n\nI‚Äôm writing this for my son as he doesn‚Äôt want other kids to experience what he saw and went through and always says what a horrible place it was for him for that one year.  He never was one of the ‚Äúbad kids‚Äù just the one witnessing how other troubled kids were treated and doesn‚Äôt feel like things were handled right.\n\nHe asked if we could give it 0 stars but unfortunately we can‚Äôt. It concerns me as a parent as he‚Äôs never been this strong about his feelings towards any of his previous daycares or after school programs.  This is why I wanted to share a review from a child‚Äôs perspective.",
