        "text": "Both our children attended this Montessori school, and I could not be happier.  The toddler program has had a noticeable impact on my youngest's concentration and behaviour - he will still be rambunctious, but at least he asks for permission before he makes a mess.  That said, being a skeptic of Montessori type environments I am now a convert to the style of learning.  It's not for every child, or parent for that matter, but it worked wonders for our children.  I really think it is the teachers that make a school, and the teachers here are outstanding.\n\nWe have since left the school (career reasons) and our children are well-prepared from their time at MCHA. More importantly, throughout the whole COVID-19 scenario we were apprized of the situation and when things opened up (w/ AHS restrictions) we reenrolled our youngest and to the best of their abilities Campus 1 and the wonderful/loving teachers were able to provide our son an island of joy and consistency in a world of turmoil and uncertainty.  We owe the wonderful folks at Campus 1 for doing such an incredible job in a very difficult time.\n\nThings were done right and we always knew our children were taken care of, always.",
