        "rating": 5,
        "relativeTimeDescription": "a month ago",
        "text": "I have waited the better part of half a decade to write this review. Our son enrolled in MCHA as soon as he was able, and tomorrow will be his last day. This is what we can tell you about this place.\n\nFirst, the head directress is CRAZY. She is absolutely bonkers about child development and squeezing every ounce of performance out of your child. She has a knack for hiring knowledgeable and caring staff, and has created a very nurturing environment for children.\n\nIn the early years, they helped greatly in potty training our child. They provided a great structure daily which I believe set a great tone for our child.\n\nLater on, that structure translated to good habits. As the education continued, our child was challenged to do his best at every turn. He started kindergarten miles ahead of his classmates, which I accredit to MCHA. he was well adjusted to a classroom environment, made friends easily, and did not struggle at all with classroom style education.\n\nThey have many family events throughout the year, and in this way, helped our son form everlasting bonds with friends. Even we as parents have met friends! Examples include: grandparents tea, daddy day, mommy day, winter carnivals, year end galas, summer picnics, etc. These events really helped to create a feeling of family, and speaking to other friends who chose other childcare options, is super rare in the industry.\n\nWe went through COVID together. While COVID made everything crazy, killed businesses, and wreaked havoc, MCHA stayed an open, and implemented great policies. Of course, at the time I didn‚Äôt think this way , and disagreed and even argued with them. In hindsight, I can recognize where I might have had the wrong idea, and while they are a business, I truly believe they made decisions based firstly on the wellbeing of the children, with profit second or third in mind.\n\nChoosing MCHA was one of the best choices I have made for my son so far. If they ever open I private school, I would be all in!\n\nThey really are that good, and we will miss them as our son grows past this stage of his life.",
