        "rating": 5,
        "relativeTimeDescription": "2 months ago",
        "text": "I'm currently a student at this school, and I love it! I just want to share my experience with those considering attending this school. However, since I am in junior high, I can't attest to other grades.\n\nTL;DR: The teachers are knowledgeable, and the school considers each student's abilities and puts them into certain classes that allow them to move at their own pace. The school also provides students with the freedom to choose some of their courses. However, there should be more communication between the administration and students, and there is a lot of homework.\nQuality of education: 10/10\nTeachers: 9/10\nSocial life: 7/10\nQuality of location: 10/10\n\nMost teachers, as not everyone can be perfect, are awesome and teach well, and are very knowledgeable in their area. I am excited to learn something new every time I go to class, and have had several in depth conversations with teachers. I also need to mention that in subjects like math and English, students are put in certain classes by their level of understanding, allowing students to move at their own pace. This has allowed me to move forward, and I am glad that the school takes each student's needs into consideration.\n\nI love the choice this school provides, with \"electives\" and \"Choice Friday\". Electives are like mini courses that different teachers offer, and students get to choose which ones they go to. While Choice Friday is when the entire Friday is filled with classes of the students' choice. These courses have allowed me to discover my interests, and it gives something to look forward to everyday. The school also provides a variety of clubs to join.\n\nNow, I want to talk a bit about the social life. The school does set up some events for students to hang out, such as school dances. Also, many students opt to spend time together in the cafeteria after classes end, so there is an active social life.\n\nHowever, I will now mention some negatives to give a weighted review. I think that there needs to be more communication between the administration and students, so students can provide feedback to the school. Also, keep in mind, especially if you are in junior high or high school, there will be a lot of homework that you will need to juggle. I know that I struggle with managing my time to get everything done.",
