        "profilePhotoUrl": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBAx_S0difh8l050h0DPwjJptOcmNAd8w1psP4gX9zpnFG=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo",
        "rating": 5,
        "relativeTimeDescription": "a year ago",
        "text": "If you are looking for a high-quality childcare program, you should really consider Seedlings. My two kids (age 4 and 2) are attending the bilingual program at the Downtown - Scarboro location, and I couldn't be happier with our choice.\n\nWhy do I recommend this daycare:\n1. Outstanding teachers - supportive, enthusiastic and genuinely caring teachers make this daycare a real gem.\n2. Excellent curriculum - daily Spanish, music, art and science (experiments) classes. They also have a big gym space, which is particularly useful for physical activities during our long winters.\n3. Small group sizes - lots of one-on-one time helps create a stronger bond between teachers and children, making the children feel safe. It also helps to develop friendships.\n4. Mixed-age groups - one of the reasons I initially decided on this daycare. I wanted my children to participate in the same program and grow together. They will have continuity of care and go through fewer transitions from caregiver to caregiver. I've noticed older children being very nurturing toward my younger child, and she learns a lot from her older peers. They support each other.\n\nMy kids truly love their teachers. Thank you, Miss April and Miss Gina, and other teachers at the Scarboro location, for taking such wonderful care of my kids!",
