        "text": "My children have been attending Somerset Child Care for the last 5 years, from infancy to kindergarten age.\n\nI can't say enough glowing things regarding our experience with the Centre and the staff who work there.  They are professional, committed to adhering to the many policies and procedures required for accreditation, but most of all, they are so loving to our boys!\n\nWhen my sensitive eldest son was struggling with the change in transitioning from the Baby room to the Toddler room, every teacher in the Centre was rooting for his success and helped to make the transition as easy as possible.  Even those teachers not involved with the rooms in question would let us know \"he's doing so much better\" and \"he's doing great\".  It made such a difference for us to know that everyone was on his side and watching out for him.  With the care and encouragement of the preschool teachers, he has blossomed from a shy boy who would not participate in organized activities/arts & crafts to an outgoing participant in all things - I give them so much credit for this transition.\n\nThe staff genuinely care about the kids in the Centre - they get to know each child's little personality quirks, interests and skills and enjoy drawing them out and celebrating them.  They also understand each child's individual challenges and help to support them through these.\n\nWhen we drop our children off each day, I am confident they are in a safe, caring environment where they will be supported, loved and have lots of fun - there is always something new going on!",
