        "rating": 5,
        "relativeTimeDescription": "2 years ago",
        "text": "Sadochok has a unique organized structure for every age group, including story time, education, outside time, music, indoor playtime, nap time and outstanding cultural learning, which are shared through concerts, family events and adorable presentations of kids that would touch your heart to see how they grow, learn and embrace the world!!! Sadochok encourages learning with daily routines and activities ranging from puzzles, to early math and reading / writing skills and even baking / cooking for special events.\nSadochok has an ability to embrace learning through play and allows kids to develop independence, pride and ability to tackle any task.  Teachers have phenomenal style that our son truly benefited from, we are more than sure that all of the kids did. It was very easy for us to notice what an amazing learning environment Sadochok has created for all the kids. Sadochok provides a safe environment for children to explore their work and socialize with other kids, but also provides an age appropriate curriculum for the preschool aged children. The techniques are extremely effective, yet firm manner, produces amazing results with the kids. It was easy to notice, that our son was performing tasks way beyond what his friends of the same age were doing at other daycare facilities and it was the key for him to successfully transition into public kindergarten. Sadochok not only teaches kids the skills necessary to perform, but it provides kids with the confidence and discipline to achieve success.  We truly believe that if we had more preschools similar to Sadochok, our children would be better prepared for school and have a better start and more success in our education system.\nThank you Sadochok for the hard work and unique style of teaching kids how to start their life adventure!  Truly wish every family has the same opportunity as we had!\n\nKind regards,\nIryna and Kevin G.",
