        "rating": 2,
        "relativeTimeDescription": "a month ago",
        "text": "Our experience with Summit Start Riverview was not great. I will say that the kids were safe and their programming seemed good. During the year and a half that we were there, lots of staff moved around, and/or left the organization. They went through five managers during the time we were there and often we were given conflicting information from one to the next. Once my son started exhibiting signs of emotional dysregulation related to his ADHD, we had 1 in person meeting, he was suspended 2 weeks later (he was part-time and had only attended 3 days within that two week period). He was 4 years old and we were told he couldn't come back until he had an aide for one-on-one care. I wasn't able to hire someone myself, they would not hire without funding, and told me it was too difficult for them to hire someone at that time. I was able to get some emergency support through Providence and they worked with Summit to determine a re-entry plan that was only a few hours a couple times a week. A few days before he was to restart, they emailed me to say they changed their mind. I wrote to complain and asked for the CEO Nancy Klensch to call me, but she never bothered (or was never told?). So not a great place for neurodiverse kids unless you already have funding in place for additional help.",
