        "rating": 1,
        "relativeTimeDescription": "2 months ago",
        "text": "We are happy to put Sunvalley behind us and put our child in school where there is consistency, with the teachers not changing every month and receiving proper communication from the staff.¬† Our experience with this centre started out great in 2021 but once the director in 2021 left and all the good teachers were forced out, it declined rapidly and continues to do so.¬† Coming to pick my child up and seeing the daily chaos in the classroom that was so dysfunctional¬†was hard to witness.¬† We had several incidents with other children and was told that a solution would be forthcoming of a quiet space for kids to go to calm down when they needed a time out and as soon as it was implemented in the form of a tent it was removed and put elsewhere as the children used it as a hang out.  No other solution was ever put forward or communicated.  I also worried for the safety of the children as the front door hasn't¬†locked let alone closed properly for the last month or more of our time there and no one seemed to have any urgency to fix it.  I mentioned it several times to staff and the director without much concern or action from anyone.¬† My child was napped until 4 1/2 years old despite my CONSTANT pleading¬†with the director and the staff to stop as I (along with many other parents) stating that my child hasn't¬†napped since 3 years old like most children and was told constantly it was for her benefit and that she wanted too.  Of course she wanted too she was being told too...!¬†This caused much regression at home and made bedtime a struggle most nights.  I communicated our frustrations and wishes to the director who always compared her younger child to mine and said \"well my child still naps and sometimes they just need it\".  I got no where.\nThey rarely did any crafts which is very sad for a pre-kindergarten program and when you are paying the annual material fee it is very disappointing.¬† All that would be ever sent home is a small scrap piece of paper with some colouring on it or a photocopied colouring picture that she had done sometimes 3-4 times already in the classroom. Needless to say my child was very bored with the lack of stimulation.  Before the decline in the centre's staff the previous teacher that was in the pre-school room (before she was forced to resign) did the most creative crafts with the kids almost¬†everyday and was so in-tune with what was going on, and the kids were so excited to attend class each day.  She would send many pictures and updates on the app per day regarding your child and now you are lucky to get a single picture during the week and most of the time it is of another child.\nLastly, the one event that my child was looking forward too was pre-k graduation as she had participated in the previous year.  I asked the director and staff regularly at the end of May and into June if it was going to happen on the date specified on the centre's calendar (June 23) and was told repeatedly that they hadn't thought about it and was told it might happen on a Friday night or a Saturday in July but they didnt know. Nonetheless, we were emailed this Monday and told that it is scheduled for this Friday night and all families are being charged for the use of the gown.  This is so disheartening to know that we were given only 4 days notice and most families will not be given the opportunity to attend due to busy summer schedules and children that have already left the centre as noted previously.  Dispite reaching out to the director she never addressed my concerns or lack of notice and planning.\nIt is very upsetting when I look back that the centre is considered Montessori but don't¬†adhere to most of the requirements with little to no structure.¬†¬†I do not recommend this centre and didn't move my child simply because of the great friends we made.  Childcare is no joke and should be taken very seriously.  We are entrusting you with our children and you should be ensuring their growth, development and most importantly safety each and everyday.  Which they have failed to do. They have alot of work to do.",
