        "text": "I have had two children attend CELC for both the preschool and childcare programs (and my baby will attend when she is old enough). We have had outstanding experiences with the school so far. The staff are caring and nurturing, and it is a very comfortable environment to leave your child. One time I was there during pick-up and my daughter had a little trip and fall and she went to her teacher for a hug even though I was there (which is a good sign to me!). They provide a good balance of structured activities and free time, with lots of age-appropriate and stimulating learning experiences for the kids. All of the staff I have interacted with are great at communication and the school has done a good job to maintain safety as well as a sense of normalcy during the COVID pandemic. I've toured many different childcare centres, and the physical space at CELC is second to none.  Preschool and childcare classrooms resemble a kindergarten learning space and are very spacious for the number of children there. They also have access to a full gym, and great outdoor playground and field.  Despite having a late birthday and being the youngest in her kindergarten and grade 1 classes, my eldest daughter was well-prepared for school as a result of her time at CELC. Highly recommend this school!",
