        "rating": 1,
        "relativeTimeDescription": "12 months ago",
        "text": "My experience with Wee Wild Ones (WWO) has been on the administrative side and with their unethical business practice of nonrefundable waitlist fees.\n\nThrough my tour of the Fairview centre in May 2022, I was led to believe that with their new Currie location opening in Sep 2022  there would be availability for my two children to attend the Fairview centre. I paid $300 to place my kids on the waitlist, which would be applied to the first month of daycare. Based on what WWO told me, I felt confident that there would be openings for my kids. However, when I contacted WWO in Oct 2022 to inquire about availability for a Dec 2022 start, I was told there were no spots open. When I asked for my $300 to be refunded since I need to find alternative childchare for Dec 2022, I was told they would not refund the $300 waitlist fee.\n\nThis is not standard practice in the childcare realm. Other daycares would only charge parents if they actually have availability. It's deplorable that WWO would charge $150/child waitlist fees for some vague promise of the possibility of placement.",
